Note: Core-model aliases (value-identical to hir.runa constants by design)
Constant HIR_IDENTIFIER as Integer is 10001          Note: Alias of core HIR_IDENTIFIER (name in value slot)
Constant HIR_LIST_LITERAL as Integer is 10011        Note: Alias of core HIR_ARRAY_LITERAL (elements in children slot)
Constant HIR_LITERAL as Integer is 10000             Note: Alias of core HIR_LITERAL (typed-literal fallback header)
Constant HIR_LITERAL_KIND_STRING as Integer is 1     Note: Core literal value_type tag: string
Constant HIR_LITERAL_KIND_BOOLEAN as Integer is 2    Note: Core literal value_type tag: boolean
Constant HIR_LITERAL_KIND_INTEGER as Integer is 3    Note: Core literal value_type tag: integer
Constant HIR_LITERAL_KIND_FLOAT as Integer is 4      Note: Core literal value_type tag: float

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Translation Accessor Foundation
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "hir_node_type" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the node kind of any translation HIR node

    @Reasoning:
    Every translation backend dispatches on the node kind; this is the
    foundational classification accessor of the surface, mirroring
    hir.runa's get_hir_node_type for consumers importing this module.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation:
    Null-guard, then read the int64 node_type at HIRNode offset 0.
    @End Implementation

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 0
End Process

Process called "hir_get_metadata" takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Read a named property from a translation HIR node

    @Reasoning:
    All named structure of translation nodes lives in the string-keyed
    property dictionary at the HIRNode metadata slot. This accessor is
    the single read path for that dictionary; every named accessor below
    delegates here with its canonical key, and frontends additionally use
    free-form language-prefixed keys (dart_async, dart_late, ...) for
    source-language idioms that have no universal slot.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation:
    Null-guard the node, read the Dictionary pointer at offset 56; if no
    dictionary has been attached return 0 (no properties set). Otherwise
    return Dict.get(dictionary, key), which is 0 for absent keys. Keys
    are compared by string content (the dictionary hashes and compares
    key text), so callers may pass any equal-text key string.
    @End Implementation

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let meta be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 56

    If meta is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc get from Dict with meta, key
End Process

Process called "hir_set_metadata" takes node as Integer, key as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Write a named property on a translation HIR node

    @Reasoning:
    Canonical write path paired with hir_get_metadata. Translation
    frontends use it both for the universal property keys documented on
    the accessors below and for language-specific flags. Creating the
    property dictionary lazily keeps property-free nodes (this, super,
    break, continue, null literal) at the bare 104-byte HIRNode cost.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation:
    Null-guard node and key. Read the Dictionary at offset 56; if absent
    create one and store it. Dict.set overwrites existing values for the
    key. Returns 1 on success, 0 on null input or allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    @Security_Scope:
    Stores key and value verbatim; pointer values must outlive the node.
    The dictionary takes no ownership of the key string beyond hashing
    and content comparison.
    @End Security_Scope

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let meta be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 56

    If meta is equal to 0:
        Set meta to proc create from Dict
        If meta is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 56, meta
    End If

    proc set from Dict with meta, key, value
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Module, Import, and Export Accessors
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "hir_get_module_name" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the library/module name of a HIR_MODULE node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_MODULE property "name" (string). 0 when the module is unnamed -
    backends treat that as "emit no library directive".
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "name"
End Process

Process called "hir_get_imports" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the import-directive List of a HIR_MODULE node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_MODULE property "imports" (List of HIR_IMPORT nodes). 0 when no
    imports were attached; List.list_length(0) is 0 so callers iterate
    safely.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "imports"
End Process

Process called "hir_get_exports" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the export-directive List of a HIR_MODULE node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_MODULE property "exports" (List of HIR_EXPORT nodes). 0 when
    absent.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "exports"
End Process

Process called "hir_get_declarations" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the top-level declaration List of a HIR_MODULE node

    @Implementation:
    Declarations are the module's primary ordered collection and live in
    the HIRNode children slot (offset 24), mirroring the core program
    root read by hir.runa's get_program_declarations. Null-guarded; 0
    when no declarations list was attached.
    @End Implementation

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 24
End Process

Process called "hir_get_import_path" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the source path of a HIR_IMPORT node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_IMPORT property "path" (string).
    @End Implementation

