Note: ============================================================================
Note: Function, Variable, and Parameter Accessors
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "hir_get_function_name" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the name of a HIR_FUNCTION node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_FUNCTION property "name" (string).
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "name"
End Process

Process called "hir_get_function_body" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the body of a HIR_FUNCTION node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_FUNCTION property "body" (HIR_BLOCK node).
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "body"
End Process

Process called "hir_get_parameters" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the parameter-collection handle of a callable node

    @Implementation:
    Callable nodes (HIR_CONSTRUCTOR, HIR_METHOD, HIR_FUNCTION,
    HIR_LAMBDA) own their parameter list directly, so the node itself is
    the collection handle; hir_get_parameter_list resolves it to the
    ordered List. Null propagates as 0.
    @End Implementation

    Return node
End Process

Process called "hir_get_parameter_list" takes params as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Resolve a parameter-collection handle to its parameter List

    @Implementation:
    Collection-handle property "parameters" (List of HIR_PARAMETER nodes
    in declaration order; positional, optional, and named parameters all
    appear in this single list, distinguished per node by the
    is_optional / is_named flags). 0 for parameterless callables.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with params, "parameters"
End Process

Process called "hir_is_parameter_named" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check whether a HIR_PARAMETER node is a named parameter

    @Implementation:
    HIR_PARAMETER property "is_named" (boolean 0/1; absent reads as 0).
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "is_named"
End Process

Process called "hir_is_parameter_optional" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check whether a HIR_PARAMETER node is optional-positional

    @Implementation:
    HIR_PARAMETER property "is_optional" (boolean 0/1; absent reads as
    0). Mutually exclusive with is_named: named parameters are already
    optional by construction.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "is_optional"
End Process

Process called "hir_get_parameter_type" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the declared type of a HIR_PARAMETER node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_PARAMETER property "type" (type node). 0 when untyped; backends
    fall back to the dynamic type.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "type"
End Process

Process called "hir_get_parameter_name" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the name of a HIR_PARAMETER node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_PARAMETER property "name" (string).
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "name"
End Process

Process called "hir_get_parameter_default" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the default-value expression of a HIR_PARAMETER node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_PARAMETER property "default_value" (expression node). 0 when the
    parameter has no default.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "default_value"
End Process

Process called "hir_is_variable_final" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check whether a HIR_VARIABLE node is final

    @Implementation:
    HIR_VARIABLE property "is_final" (boolean 0/1; absent reads as 0).
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "is_final"
End Process

Process called "hir_is_variable_const" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Check whether a HIR_VARIABLE node is const

    @Implementation:
    HIR_VARIABLE property "is_const" (boolean 0/1; absent reads as 0).
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "is_const"
End Process

Process called "hir_get_variable_type" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the declared type of a HIR_VARIABLE node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_VARIABLE property "type" (type node). 0 when untyped.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "type"
End Process

Process called "hir_get_variable_name" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the name of a HIR_VARIABLE node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_VARIABLE property "name" (string).
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "name"
End Process

Process called "hir_get_variable_initializer" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the initializer expression of a HIR_VARIABLE node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_VARIABLE property "initializer" (expression node). 0 when the
    variable is declared without a value.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "initializer"
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Function, Variable, and Parameter Producers (Task #436)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "hir_create_function" returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_FUNCTION declaration node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_FUNCTION. The "name", "body",
    "return_type", "type_parameters", and "parameters" properties are
    attached by the paired setters and adders; the node itself is the
    parameter-collection handle per hir_get_parameters. Returns 0 on
    allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_FUNCTION, 0, 0
End Process

Process called "hir_set_function_name" takes node as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the name of a HIR_FUNCTION node

    @Implementation:
    Writes HIR_FUNCTION property "name" (string) - the key
    hir_get_function_name reads. Returns 1 on success, 0 on null input
    or allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_set_metadata with node, "name", name
End Process

Process called "hir_set_function_body" takes node as Integer, body as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the body of a HIR_FUNCTION node

    @Implementation:
    Writes HIR_FUNCTION property "body" (HIR_BLOCK node) - the key
    hir_get_function_body reads. Returns 1 on success, 0 on null input
    or allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_set_metadata with node, "body", body
End Process

Process called "hir_create_parameter" returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_PARAMETER declaration node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_PARAMETER. The "name", "type",
    "default_value", "is_named", and "is_optional" properties are
    attached by the paired setters. Returns 0 on allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_PARAMETER, 0, 0
End Process

Process called "hir_set_parameter_name" takes node as Integer, name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the name of a HIR_PARAMETER node

    @Implementation:
    Writes HIR_PARAMETER property "name" (string) - the key
    hir_get_parameter_name reads. Returns 1 on success, 0 on null input
    or allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_set_metadata with node, "name", name
End Process

Process called "hir_set_parameter_type" takes node as Integer, parameter_type as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the declared type of a HIR_PARAMETER node

    @Implementation:
    Writes HIR_PARAMETER property "type" (type node) - the key
    hir_get_parameter_type reads. Returns 1 on success, 0 on null input
    or allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_set_metadata with node, "type", parameter_type
End Process

Process called "hir_set_parameter_default" takes node as Integer, default_value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the default-value expression of a HIR_PARAMETER node

    @Implementation:
    Writes HIR_PARAMETER property "default_value" (expression node) -
    the key hir_get_parameter_default reads. Returns 1 on success, 0 on
    null input or allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_set_metadata with node, "default_value", default_value
End Process

Process called "hir_set_parameter_named" takes node as Integer, is_named as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the named flag of a HIR_PARAMETER node

    @Implementation:
    Writes HIR_PARAMETER property "is_named" (boolean 0/1) - the key
    hir_is_parameter_named reads. Mutually exclusive with is_optional by
    the parameter model; producers set at most one of the two flags.
    Returns 1 on success, 0 on null input or allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_set_metadata with node, "is_named", is_named
End Process

Process called "hir_set_parameter_optional" takes node as Integer, is_optional as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the optional-positional flag of a HIR_PARAMETER node

    @Implementation:
    Writes HIR_PARAMETER property "is_optional" (boolean 0/1) - the key
    hir_is_parameter_optional reads. Returns 1 on success, 0 on null
    input or allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_set_metadata with node, "is_optional", is_optional
End Process

Process called "hir_add_parameter" takes node as Integer, parameter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Append a positional parameter to a callable node

    @Implementation:
    Appends to the callable's property "parameters" (the single ordered
    List hir_get_parameter_list resolves; the callable node is its own
    collection handle), creating the List on first use. Declaration
    order is preserved. Returns 1 on success, 0 on null input or
    allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If parameter is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let parameters be proc hir_get_metadata with node, "parameters"

    If parameters is equal to 0:
        Set parameters to proc create from List
        If parameters is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Let stored be proc hir_set_metadata with node, "parameters", parameters
        If stored is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    proc append from List with parameters, parameter
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "hir_add_named_parameter" takes node as Integer, parameter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Append a named parameter to a callable node

    @Implementation:
    Sets the parameter's "is_named" flag (the key
    hir_is_parameter_named reads) so the flag and list membership can
    never disagree, then appends to the same single "parameters" List as
    hir_add_parameter - named parameters are distinguished per node, not
    by a separate collection. Returns 1 on success, 0 on null input or
    allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    If parameter is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let flagged be proc hir_set_metadata with parameter, "is_named", 1
    If flagged is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc hir_add_parameter with node, parameter
End Process

Process called "hir_add_optional_parameter" takes node as Integer, parameter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Append an optional-positional parameter to a callable node

    @Implementation:
    Sets the parameter's "is_optional" flag (the key
    hir_is_parameter_optional reads) so the flag and list membership can
    never disagree, then appends to the same single "parameters" List as
    hir_add_parameter. Returns 1 on success, 0 on null input or
    allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    If parameter is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let flagged be proc hir_set_metadata with parameter, "is_optional", 1
    If flagged is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc hir_add_parameter with node, parameter
End Process

