Note: ============================================================================
Note: Statement Accessors
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "hir_get_block_statements" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the statement List of a HIR_BLOCK node

    @Implementation:
    Statements are the block's primary ordered collection and live in
    the HIRNode children slot (offset 24), mirroring core
    HIR_BLOCK_STATEMENT storage so generic tree walkers traverse both
    block kinds identically. Null-guarded; 0 for empty blocks built
    without a statements list.
    @End Implementation

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 24
End Process

Process called "hir_get_expression_statement_expr" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the wrapped expression of a HIR_EXPR_STMT node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_EXPR_STMT property "expression" (expression node).
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "expression"
End Process

Process called "hir_get_return_value" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the returned expression of a HIR_RETURN node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_RETURN property "value" (expression node). 0 for a bare void
    return - backends emit the value-less form in that case.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "value"
End Process

Process called "hir_get_if_condition" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the condition of a HIR_IF node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_IF property "condition" (expression node).
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "condition"
