    or allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_set_metadata with node, "exception_type", exception_type
End Process

Process called "hir_set_catch_variable" takes node as Integer, exception_variable as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the exception variable name of a HIR_CATCH node

    @Implementation:
    Writes HIR_CATCH property "exception_variable" (string) - the key
    hir_get_catch_variable reads. Returns 1 on success, 0 on null input
    or allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_set_metadata with node, "exception_variable", exception_variable
End Process

Process called "hir_set_catch_body" takes node as Integer, body as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the handler body of a HIR_CATCH node

    @Implementation:
    Writes HIR_CATCH property "body" (statement node) - the key
    hir_get_catch_body reads. Returns 1 on success, 0 on null input or
    allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_set_metadata with node, "body", body
End Process

Process called "hir_create_throw" returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_THROW statement node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_THROW. The "expression" property is
    attached via hir_set_throw_expression. Returns 0 on allocation
    failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_THROW, 0, 0
End Process

Process called "hir_set_throw_expression" takes node as Integer, expression as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the thrown expression of a HIR_THROW node

    @Implementation:
    Writes HIR_THROW property "expression" (expression node) - the key
    hir_get_throw_expression reads. Returns 1 on success, 0 on null
    input or allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_set_metadata with node, "expression", expression
End Process

Process called "hir_create_break" returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_BREAK statement node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_BREAK. Break is a payload-free marker
    statement, so no properties are attached and the node stays at the
    bare 104-byte cost. Returns 0 on allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_BREAK, 0, 0
End Process

Process called "hir_create_continue" returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_CONTINUE statement node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_CONTINUE. Continue is a payload-free
    marker statement, so no properties are attached. Returns 0 on
    allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_CONTINUE, 0, 0
End Process

Process called "hir_create_assert" returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_ASSERT statement node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_ASSERT. The "condition" and optional
    "message" properties are attached by the paired setters. Returns 0
    on allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_ASSERT, 0, 0
End Process

Process called "hir_set_assert_condition" takes node as Integer, condition as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the asserted condition of a HIR_ASSERT node

    @Implementation:
    Writes HIR_ASSERT property "condition" (expression node) - the key
    hir_get_assert_condition reads. Returns 1 on success, 0 on null
    input or allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_set_metadata with node, "condition", condition
End Process

Process called "hir_set_assert_message" takes node as Integer, message as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the failure message of a HIR_ASSERT node

    @Implementation:
    Writes HIR_ASSERT property "message" (expression node) - the key
    hir_get_assert_message reads. Asserts without a message never call
    this setter. Returns 1 on success, 0 on null input or allocation
    failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_set_metadata with node, "message", message
End Process

Process called "hir_create_yield" returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_YIELD statement node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_YIELD. The "expression" property is
    attached via hir_set_yield_expression; the yield-each variant is
    flagged through language metadata (dart_yield_each). Returns 0 on
    allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_YIELD, 0, 0
End Process

Process called "hir_set_yield_expression" takes node as Integer, expression as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the yielded expression of a HIR_YIELD node

    @Implementation:
    Writes HIR_YIELD property "expression" (expression node) - the key
    hir_get_yield_expression reads. Returns 1 on success, 0 on null
    input or allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_set_metadata with node, "expression", expression
End Process

Process called "hir_create_nop" returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_NOP statement node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_NOP - the payload-free no-operation
    statement frontends emit for unrecognized statement kinds so the
    surrounding block keeps a valid statement slot. Returns 0 on
    allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_NOP, 0, 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Literal and Identifier Accessors
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "hir_get_int_literal_value" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the int64 payload of an integer literal node

    @Implementation:
    Accepts both encodings: a translation HIR_INT_LITERAL node, and a
    core HIR_LITERAL node whose value_type tag is integer. Both store
    the raw int64 in the value slot (offset 40). Wrong kinds return 0.
    @End Implementation

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 0

    If node_kind is equal to HIR_INT_LITERAL:
        Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 40
    End If

    If node_kind is equal to HIR_LITERAL:
        Let value_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 48
        If value_kind is equal to HIR_LITERAL_KIND_INTEGER:
            Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 40
        End If
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Process called "hir_get_float_literal_value" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the IEEE-754 bit payload of a float literal node

    @Implementation:
    Accepts both encodings: a translation HIR_FLOAT_LITERAL node, and a
    core HIR_LITERAL node whose value_type tag is float. Both store the
    float bit pattern in the value slot (offset 40). Wrong kinds
    return 0.
    @End Implementation

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 0

    If node_kind is equal to HIR_FLOAT_LITERAL:
        Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 40
    End If

    If node_kind is equal to HIR_LITERAL:
        Let value_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 48
        If value_kind is equal to HIR_LITERAL_KIND_FLOAT:
            Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 40
        End If
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Process called "hir_get_string_literal_value" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the string payload of a string literal node

    @Implementation:
    Accepts both encodings: a translation HIR_STRING_LITERAL node, and a
    core HIR_LITERAL node whose value_type tag is string. Both store the
    string pointer in the value slot (offset 40). Wrong kinds return 0.
    @End Implementation

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 0

    If node_kind is equal to HIR_STRING_LITERAL:
        Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 40
    End If

    If node_kind is equal to HIR_LITERAL:
        Let value_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 48
        If value_kind is equal to HIR_LITERAL_KIND_STRING:
            Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 40
        End If
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Process called "hir_get_bool_literal_value" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the 0/1 payload of a boolean literal node

    @Implementation:
    Accepts both encodings: a translation HIR_BOOL_LITERAL node, and a
    core HIR_LITERAL node whose value_type tag is boolean. Both store
    0 or 1 in the value slot (offset 40). Wrong kinds return 0.
    @End Implementation

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 0

    If node_kind is equal to HIR_BOOL_LITERAL:
        Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 40
    End If

    If node_kind is equal to HIR_LITERAL:
        Let value_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 48
        If value_kind is equal to HIR_LITERAL_KIND_BOOLEAN:
            Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 40
        End If
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Process called "hir_get_identifier_name" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the name string of a HIR_IDENTIFIER node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_IDENTIFIER is value-aliased to the core identifier kind, whose
    name lives in the HIRNode value slot (offset 40) - the layout
    created by hir.runa's create_hir_identifier. Kind-validated; wrong
    kinds return 0.
    @End Implementation

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 0
    If node_kind is not equal to HIR_IDENTIFIER:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 40
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Literal and Identifier Producers (Task #436)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "hir_create_int_literal" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_INT_LITERAL expression node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_INT_LITERAL with the raw int64 payload
    in the value slot (offset 40) and the core integer tag
    (HIR_LITERAL_KIND_INTEGER) in the value_type slot (offset 48) - the
    dual encoding hir_get_int_literal_value accepts, keeping translation
    literals interchangeable with core-built literals. Returns 0 on
    allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Let node be proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_INT_LITERAL, 0, 0

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 40, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 48, HIR_LITERAL_KIND_INTEGER

    Return node
End Process

Process called "hir_create_float_literal" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_FLOAT_LITERAL expression node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_FLOAT_LITERAL with the IEEE-754 binary64
    bit pattern (carried as int64, the compiler-wide float convention) in
    the value slot (offset 40) and HIR_LITERAL_KIND_FLOAT in the
    value_type slot (offset 48) - the encoding
    hir_get_float_literal_value reads. Returns 0 on allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Let node be proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_FLOAT_LITERAL, 0, 0

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 40, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 48, HIR_LITERAL_KIND_FLOAT

    Return node
End Process

Process called "hir_create_string_literal" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_STRING_LITERAL expression node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_STRING_LITERAL with the string pointer
    in the value slot (offset 40) and HIR_LITERAL_KIND_STRING in the
    value_type slot (offset 48) - the encoding
    hir_get_string_literal_value reads. The pointer is stored verbatim;
    the string must outlive the node (automatic under arena ownership).
    Returns 0 on allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Let node be proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_STRING_LITERAL, 0, 0

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 40, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 48, HIR_LITERAL_KIND_STRING

    Return node
End Process

Process called "hir_create_bool_literal" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_BOOL_LITERAL expression node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_BOOL_LITERAL with the truth value
    normalized to exactly 0 or 1 in the value slot (offset 40) and
    HIR_LITERAL_KIND_BOOLEAN in the value_type slot (offset 48) - the
    encoding hir_get_bool_literal_value reads. Normalization guarantees
    backends can compare the payload against 1 directly. Returns 0 on
    allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Let node be proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_BOOL_LITERAL, 0, 0

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let normalized be 0
    If value is not equal to 0:
        Set normalized to 1
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 40, normalized
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 48, HIR_LITERAL_KIND_BOOLEAN

    Return node
End Process

Process called "hir_create_null_literal" returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_NULL_LITERAL expression node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_NULL_LITERAL. Null carries no payload,
    so the value and value_type slots stay zero-initialized. Returns 0
    on allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_NULL_LITERAL, 0, 0
End Process

Process called "hir_create_identifier" takes name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_IDENTIFIER expression node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_IDENTIFIER is value-aliased to the core identifier kind, so this
    delegates to hir.runa's create_hir_identifier, which stores the name
    in the value slot (offset 40) - the layout hir_get_identifier_name
    reads. Core-built and translation-built identifiers are therefore
    bit-identical. Returns 0 on allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc create_hir_identifier from HIR with name
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Expression Accessors
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "hir_get_binary_op" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the operator code of a HIR_BINARY_EXPR node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_BINARY_EXPR property "operator" (HIR_OP_* code). Absent reads as
    0, which no operator code uses, so backends fall through to their
    default mapping.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc hir_get_metadata with node, "operator"
End Process

Process called "hir_get_binary_left" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get the left operand of a HIR_BINARY_EXPR node

