Process called "hir_create_binary_expr" takes operator as Integer, left as Integer, right as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_BINARY_EXPR expression node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_BINARY_EXPR with properties "operator"
    (HIR_OP_* code), "left", and "right" (expression nodes) set at
    construction - the keys hir_get_binary_op, hir_get_binary_left, and
    hir_get_binary_right read. Returns 0 on allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Let node be proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_BINARY_EXPR, 0, 0

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc hir_set_metadata with node, "operator", operator
    proc hir_set_metadata with node, "left", left
    proc hir_set_metadata with node, "right", right

    Return node
End Process

