Process called "hir_create_assign_expr" takes lhs as Integer, operator as Integer, rhs as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_ASSIGN_EXPR expression node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_ASSIGN_EXPR with properties "lhs"
    (lvalue expression node), "operator" (HIR_ASSIGN_* code), and "rhs"
    (expression node) set at construction - the keys hir_get_assign_lhs,
    hir_get_assign_op, and hir_get_assign_rhs read. Returns 0 on
    allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Let node be proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_ASSIGN_EXPR, 0, 0

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc hir_set_metadata with node, "lhs", lhs
    proc hir_set_metadata with node, "operator", operator
    proc hir_set_metadata with node, "rhs", rhs

    Return node
End Process

Process called "hir_create_list_literal" returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_LIST_LITERAL expression node

    @Implementation:
    HIR_LIST_LITERAL is value-aliased to the core array literal, so this
    delegates to hir.runa's create_hir_list_literal, which eagerly
    creates the elements List in the children slot (offset 24) - the
    layout hir_get_list_elements reads. Returns 0 on allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc create_hir_list_literal from HIR
End Process

Process called "hir_add_list_element" takes node as Integer, element as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Append an element to a HIR_LIST_LITERAL node

    @Implementation:
    Delegates to hir.runa's add_list_element so core-built and
    translation-built list literals share one append/count/parent
    bookkeeping path over the children slot. Returns 1 on success, 0 on
    null input.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc add_list_element from HIR with node, element
End Process

Process called "hir_create_map_literal" returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_MAP_LITERAL expression node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_MAP_LITERAL (expression-keyed, distinct
    from string-keyed core dictionary literals) with an eagerly created
    entries List in the children slot (offset 24) - the collection
    hir_get_map_entries reads and hir_add_map_entry appends to. Returns
    0 on allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Let node be proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_MAP_LITERAL, 0, 0

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let entries be proc create from List
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 24, entries

    Return node
End Process

Process called "hir_add_map_entry" takes node as Integer, key as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Append a key/value entry to a HIR_MAP_LITERAL node

    @Implementation:
    Kind-validates the node, then materializes a 16-byte entry block
    laid out [key(0), value(8)] where BOTH halves are expression nodes -
    the layout hir_get_map_entry_key and hir_get_map_entry_value read -
    and appends it to the entries List in the children slot, creating
    the List when absent. child_count at offset 32 tracks the entry
    count. Returns 1 on success, 0 on null/wrong-kind input or
    allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let node_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 0
    If node_kind is not equal to HIR_MAP_LITERAL:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let entry be proc allocate from Layout with 16
    If entry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with entry, 0, key
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with entry, 8, value

    Let entries be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 24
    If entries is equal to 0:
        Set entries to proc create from List
        If entries is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 24, entries
    End If

    proc append from List with entries, entry

    Let count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 32
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with node, 32, count plus 1

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "hir_create_lambda" returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_LAMBDA expression node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_LAMBDA. The body is attached via
    exactly one of hir_set_lambda_expression_body or
    hir_set_lambda_block_body (which also maintain the
    "has_expression_body" flag); parameters are attached via the
    parameter adders - the lambda is its own parameter-collection handle
    per hir_get_lambda_parameters. Returns 0 on allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_LAMBDA, 0, 0
End Process

Process called "hir_set_lambda_expression_body" takes node as Integer, body as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the arrow (expression) body of a HIR_LAMBDA node

    @Implementation:
    Writes HIR_LAMBDA property "expression_body" (expression node, the
    key hir_get_lambda_expression_body reads) and sets
    "has_expression_body" to 1 (the flag hir_has_lambda_expression_body
    reads) in the same call so the pair can never disagree. Returns 1 on
    success, 0 on null input or allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Let stored be proc hir_set_metadata with node, "expression_body", body

    If stored is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc hir_set_metadata with node, "has_expression_body", 1
End Process

Process called "hir_set_lambda_block_body" takes node as Integer, body as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Set the block body of a HIR_LAMBDA node

    @Implementation:
    Writes HIR_LAMBDA property "block_body" (HIR_BLOCK node, the key
    hir_get_lambda_block_body reads) and sets "has_expression_body" to 0
    in the same call so the flag and body storage stay consistent even
    if a frontend rewrites an arrow lambda into block form. Returns 1 on
    success, 0 on null input or allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Let stored be proc hir_set_metadata with node, "block_body", body

    If stored is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc hir_set_metadata with node, "has_expression_body", 0
End Process

Process called "hir_create_await" takes expression as Integer returns Integer:
