Process called "hir_create_this" returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_THIS self-reference expression node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_THIS. Self-reference is payload-free,
    so no properties are attached and the node stays at the bare
    104-byte cost. Returns 0 on allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_THIS, 0, 0
End Process

Process called "hir_create_super" returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_SUPER base-reference expression node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_SUPER. Base-reference is payload-free,
    so no properties are attached. Returns 0 on allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Return proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_SUPER, 0, 0
End Process

Process called "hir_create_error" takes message as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create a HIR_ERROR recovery sentinel node

    @Implementation:
    Standard HIRNode of kind HIR_ERROR with property "message" (string
    describing what the frontend could not translate, readable through
    hir_get_metadata with key "message"). Frontends emit this sentinel
    instead of a null pointer so the surrounding tree stays walkable
    during error recovery. Returns 0 on allocation failure.
    @End Implementation

    Let node be proc create_hir_node from HIR with HIR_ERROR, 0, 0

    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If message is not equal to 0:
        proc hir_set_metadata with node, "message", message
    End If

    Return node
End Process

